Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.06,0:00:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my friend Saki Marais,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.39,0:00:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Writing Committee\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s here to help me discuss\Nthe gifts we present to Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.03,0:00:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Saki, can you tell us\Nwhat the program is all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.27,0:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll meet Sister Lillian Barnes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of our age,\Nwe can learn from her example
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.81,0:00:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of loyal endurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.15,0:00:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What Bible counsel for young ones\Ncontinues to motivate her
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.48,0:00:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve Jehovah whole-souled?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.22,0:00:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll go to the United States branch
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.22,0:00:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in Wallkill, New York,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.29,0:00:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to see how they produce Braille Bibles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.53,0:00:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How has the revised\NNew World Translation in Braille helped
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.87,0:00:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,these brothers and sisters\Ngive their gifts to God?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.94,0:00:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is physical cleanliness
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.94,0:01:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,an important part of our clean worship?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.41,0:01:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll find out in this dramatization
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.15,0:01:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Principles for Daily Living series.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.65,0:01:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the April 2019 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.89,0:01:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.41,0:01:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This month I’d like to talk\Nabout “Presenting Your Gifts to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.41,0:01:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We certainly have every reason\Nto consider this topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.28,0:01:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.22,0:01:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because Jehovah gives us so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.59,0:01:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,James 1:17 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.36,0:01:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Every good gift\Nand every perfect present is from above,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,coming down\Nfrom the Father of the celestial lights.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.57,0:02:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\NJehovah allows us to enjoy the gift of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.11,0:02:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,even though our first parents\Ntried to take that from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.11,0:02:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s provided us with a variety of foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The environment is just right to support life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.35,0:02:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s given us his precious Word, the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.66,0:02:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can come to know\Nhim and his purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.23,0:02:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the greatest “perfect present”\NJehovah has given us is the ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.23,0:02:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sacrificed\Na great deal to arrange for Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.60,0:02:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to buy back for us the hope of everlasting life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.54,0:02:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This was at no obligation on Jehovah’s part.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.18,0:02:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was totally a gift of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.95,0:02:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Please read with me 1 John 4:9:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.75,0:02:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“By this the love of God\Nwas revealed in our case,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“that God sent\Nhis only-begotten Son into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we might gain life through him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What a gift of love from Jehovah, our God!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.13,0:03:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that move us to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.40,0:03:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’ve had the experience\Nof a close friend or family member
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.50,0:03:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,unexpectedly giving you a valuable gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.74,0:03:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, what are you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.51,0:03:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You are probably trying to think\Nof what you can give in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.42,0:03:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How much more so\Nwould we want to ‘present our gifts to God’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to show\Nour sincere appreciation for all he’s done!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider some possible gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.33,0:03:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah\Nwould be pleased to receive from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.37,0:03:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you in our viewing audience
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.57,0:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have been moved to give your life to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicating yourself to do his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s commendable!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.68,0:03:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Romans 12 urges us to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there are some of you listening
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.45,0:03:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who have thought\Nabout this way of giving back to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.72,0:04:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but you haven’t yet taken this vital step.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.26,0:04:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice the appeal the apostle Paul makes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at Romans 12:1:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.96,0:04:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, I appeal to you\Nby the compassions of God, brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.93,0:04:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“to present your bodies as a living sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.37,0:04:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“holy and acceptable to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.51,0:04:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a sacred service with your power of reason.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life is precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Presenting your body, your whole soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to God is one of the best gifts\Nyou can give to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.62,0:04:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This involves our sacred service to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.76,0:04:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.76,0:04:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about the daily activities of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.83,0:04:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you do housework on a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.63,0:04:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Others of you have\Nschool to attend and homework to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.64,0:04:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you perform secular work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.34,0:04:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s shopping to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.44,0:04:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Others enjoy using\Na small percentage of their time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.21,0:04:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to engage in some type\Nof recreation or entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.05,0:05:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you’re dedicated and baptized,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.59,0:05:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this is all part of your gift to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.09,0:05:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please consider with me
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.09,0:05:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Colossians 3:23, 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,After discussing\Na whole list of daily activities of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what does Jehovah tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.97,0:05:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Colossians 3:23, 24:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whatever you are doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.84,0:05:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“work at it whole-souled as for Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“and not for men,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“for you know that it is from Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you will receive the inheritance as a reward.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.25,0:05:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that a Christian’s day-to-day activities
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.92,0:05:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are not part of his sacred service.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the fact that Paul urges us
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.46,0:05:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to work “whole-souled as to Jehovah”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.20,0:05:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,makes us think of our entire course of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.50,0:05:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our life course\Ncan become a gift presented to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, do we act and dress\Nwith proper decorum at all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.48,0:06:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Understandably,\Nwe don’t wear a suit and tie or a dress
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for every activity of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.25,0:06:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But in “whatever you are doing,”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is your behavior and dress a gift to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.66,0:06:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If while engaging in any activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d be embarrassed to identify\Nourselves as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then can we really claim to be presenting
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.44,0:06:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a gift to Jehovah in our daily life?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.71,0:06:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What other gifts are in our possession\Nthat we can present to God?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What about godly morality?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping your dedicated body clean morally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.89,0:06:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is a gift to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.29,0:06:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice what Romans 12:1 said?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It said that the bodies we present to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.03,0:06:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,should be “holy and acceptable to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.44,0:07:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If we give in to temptation unrepentantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.61,0:07:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that could be likened to asking Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.01,0:07:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to give our gift back;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.38,0:07:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re taking back our dedicated life from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.08,0:07:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Worse yet, it is tantamount\Nto taking the gift away from Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.69,0:07:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and giving that precious gift to Satan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.99,0:07:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That does not make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.83,0:07:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep clean morally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.90,0:07:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a precious gift presented to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.33,0:07:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true, when we’re dedicated and baptized,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,there are other gifts that we’d be expected
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.77,0:07:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to present to Jehovah on a regular basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the most obvious ways
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.45,0:07:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is mentioned here at Hebrews 10:23.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.68,0:07:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you already guess\Nwhat this gift to Jehovah would be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.49,0:07:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 10:23:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:08:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let us hold firmly the public declaration\Nof our hope without wavering,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.03,0:08:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for the one who promised is faithful.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.47,0:08:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The public declaration of our hope
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.27,0:08:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is a gift to those we speak to,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s also considered\Na gift extended to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.01,0:08:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,\NHebrews 13:15 calls our preaching work
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.78,0:08:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“a sacrifice of praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.59,0:08:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“that is, the fruit of our lips
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.22,0:08:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that make public declaration to his name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.79,0:08:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Israelites used to regularly offer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.56,0:08:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the best of their animals or grain
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.73,0:08:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as sacrificial gifts to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharing in the ministry formally or informally
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.94,0:08:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is a gift to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Regularly attending our Christian meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.84,0:08:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and participating in them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.85,0:08:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of our worship and pleases Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.02,0:08:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We are familiar with Hebrews 10:24, 25.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.02,0:09:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It speaks of our custom of meeting together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.36,0:09:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And for what purpose do we meet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.03,0:09:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was there in your home with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.10,0:09:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,how would you answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.10,0:09:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You might quickly say,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.10,0:09:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“I go to the meetings to be built up\Nand to be encouraged spiritually.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.91,0:09:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no doubt you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.54,0:09:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But at Hebrews 10:24, 25,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.11,0:09:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of attending is expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.65,0:09:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in a totally different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.58,0:09:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of going\Nwith the sole intent of being encouraged,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.59,0:09:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 24 says
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.69,0:09:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we are to “consider one another
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.16,0:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“so as to incite [others]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.00,0:09:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to love and fine works.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 25 says
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.87,0:09:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we are to be “encouraging one another.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.84,0:09:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We should attend our meetings\Nwith the goal of being a gift to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.71,0:10:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Encouraging others is the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.02,0:10:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this by our sincere interest in others
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.55,0:10:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,before and after the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you come to the Kingdom Hall early
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.89,0:10:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage others?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.99,0:10:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When in the traveling work, years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.60,0:10:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,my wife and I drove in to the parking lot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.83,0:10:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and got out of our car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.77,0:10:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Two brothers approached us and warmly said:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.17,0:10:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Brother and Sister Herd,\Nwe were waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.38,0:10:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We are so happy to have you\Nwith our congregation this week.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.32,0:10:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Were they elders,\Nministerial servants, or pioneers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.32,0:10:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they were two little preteenage boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.13,0:10:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That boost gave us a fine start
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.93,0:10:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for a special week of activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We also encourage others\Nby participating in the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.47,0:10:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What an encouragement\Nto the whole congregation!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.11,0:11:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, if we all go to the meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.71,0:11:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with that goal and motive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what will be the result to us individually?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We all will come away built up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.09,0:11:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and encouraged spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But we must never forget
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.59,0:11:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that being at our Christian meetings\Nand participating,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.80,0:11:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,including singing the songs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.70,0:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying “Amen” to the prayers,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually worshipping Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.31,0:11:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You are presenting a gift to him\Nat every meeting you attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.24,0:11:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,From ancient times until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.35,0:11:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s faithful servants\Nhave contributed materially
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.35,0:11:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to the support of true worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s presenting a gift to God as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.12,0:11:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and we thank all of you for your support.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.16,0:11:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body is able to provide so much
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.50,0:11:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for the benefit of the worldwide brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.47,0:12:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because of your generosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.97,0:12:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you Christian parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.11,0:12:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What gift can you present to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.58,0:12:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Your children!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.25,0:12:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When you do your best to ‘bring your children up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.22,0:12:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the discipline and admonition of Jehovah,’
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.42,0:12:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you are preparing a gift to your God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.69,0:12:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the number of brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.69,0:12:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,taking the lead in the organization at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.60,0:12:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are Governing Body members, helpers,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.40,0:12:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Branch Committee members, circuit overseers,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.14,0:12:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,elders, and ministerial servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.44,0:12:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did so many of these come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of thousands\Nwere children of Christian parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.35,0:12:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The parents followed\Nthe admonition of Ephesians 6:4.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There are thousands more brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.06,0:12:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been raised\Nin the truth by godly parents
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.83,0:13:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who are spearheading\Nthe work in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.47,0:13:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in Bethel service,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.50,0:13:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on construction projects, and in relief work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.64,0:13:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank you, parents,\Nfor all that you’ve done
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.94,0:13:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the precious gifts\Nyou have offered up to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.54,0:13:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and his organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.55,0:13:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about the older ones\Nin our congregations?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.92,0:13:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m 84 years young with eternity in view.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.75,0:13:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But at some point,\Nwe start to admit that we’re getting old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We start to feel that we’re getting old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.26,0:13:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We start to look like we’re getting old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.23,0:13:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of us find ourselves\Nslipping physically or even mentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.24,0:13:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we becoming\Nless and less valuable to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.71,0:13:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is our gift now tarnished by age?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.11,0:13:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We might begin to think so,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.28,0:13:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but that’s not at all how\NJehovah views older ones
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.29,0:14:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who have dedicated themselves to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.12,0:14:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,possibly many decades ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A tarnished gold coin
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has as much value as a shiny new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.10,0:14:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 16:31 instructs us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.64,0:14:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that “gray hair is a crown of beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when it is found in the way of righteousness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.28,0:14:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not so much the color\Nof the hair that Jehovah admires.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.02,0:14:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it’s the life of self-sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.49,0:14:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that gray hair represents.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.85,0:14:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah views older ones
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.22,0:14:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who are still found in the way of righteousness
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.53,0:14:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as precious gifts to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.86,0:14:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do pieces of antique furniture often cost
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.50,0:14:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,much more than a brand new piece of furniture?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.20,0:14:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Or why is an older bottle of fine wine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.68,0:14:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,often more expensive\Nthan a newer vintage wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.55,0:15:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Age brings value to a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.62,0:15:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You older ones have wisdom and experience
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.62,0:15:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that others in the congregation can benefit from.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.19,0:15:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not that you\Nneed to be holding the microphone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and waxing eloquent\Non every paragraph at a meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.87,0:15:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but modestly sharing your experience
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and wisdom with others on a personal basis
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.64,0:15:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can be so helpful and encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves you older ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.11,0:15:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you’re bent with age in your mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.12,0:15:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,stand tall as a precious gift\Npresented to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.59,0:15:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,May all of us, young and old,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.29,0:15:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,consider how we can enhance\Nour gifts presented to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If we have not yet dedicated our life to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.90,0:15:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is it time to seriously consider this gift?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.01,0:16:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we enhance our gift
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.01,0:16:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by more closely monitoring \Nour view of Christian morality?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.95,0:16:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What we look at or think about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,could compromise our gift to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How about our ministry or attendance\Nand participation at the meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.12,0:16:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,or contributing materially
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to the worldwide work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,do your best to package
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.30,0:16:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the gift of your children
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.74,0:16:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they will be useful to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.34,0:16:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And you older ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,never forget that when it comes\Nto wisdom and experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.35,0:16:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you only get better with age.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is the best of Jehovah’s servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.55,0:16:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s been around the longest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s meet a sister who’s applied the counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.83,0:16:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve God from her youth on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.37,0:16:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Lillian Barnes is from Jamaica.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.90,0:17:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Her gifts to Jehovah \Nmay have changed with age,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.74,0:17:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but what she gives to him today
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.18,0:17:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is in no way less valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.20,0:21:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.21,0:21:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“your Grand Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.81,0:21:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the days of your youth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.88,0:21:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Sister Barnes’ determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Lillian is now 108 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.58,0:21:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and has been baptized for nearly 82 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.42,0:21:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Her beautiful example shows the contentment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.49,0:21:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes from serving God\Nwhole-souled at any age.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.43,0:21:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To give Jehovah our best,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we need God’s Word\Nto know how to worship him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.33,0:22:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why Jehovah’s organization works hard
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.67,0:22:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the Bible available\Nto as many people as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.24,0:22:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At the United States branch\Nin Wallkill, New York,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.11,0:22:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they are producing Braille copies
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.68,0:22:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of the revised New World Translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.75,0:22:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it take\Nto make a good quality Braille Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.56,0:22:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and how are Braille readers\Nusing this beautiful gift?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.43,0:22:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2013, our English-printed Bibles
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.87,0:22:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,were revised and, shortly thereafter,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.37,0:22:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the Braille Bibles were approved
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.44,0:22:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to be revised in English and Portuguese.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.94,0:22:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew it was going to be a large job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.81,0:22:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We were having problems
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.71,0:22:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with the pages either tearing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.71,0:22:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,or coming completely out of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.05,0:22:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried changing the paper\Nto see if that would be a simple solution,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.15,0:22:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had a brother\Nwho is blind come in and help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.06,0:22:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We were able to test the paper\Nin the machine and actually walk it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.13,0:23:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,right over to the brother,\Nand he gave us immediate feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.03,0:23:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,on adjustments to the machine
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.70,0:23:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or if it wasn’t working at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.20,0:23:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,During our testing,\Nwe tried about 25 different types of paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.81,0:23:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but we ended up coming back to the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.04,0:23:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that the binding was\Nthe best way to find a durable solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.81,0:23:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The result is that the durability
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.72,0:23:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is 400 percent stronger than it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.92,0:23:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pick up an entire book
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.52,0:23:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,by holding just one page.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.99,0:23:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Literature Production Office,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.16,0:23:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we have ones who receive
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.39,0:23:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the requests for the Braille Bibles,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.20,0:23:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we have ones\Nwho will review these requests
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.87,0:23:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as they come into the system,\Nand then we have
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.53,0:23:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a separate set of brothers who make sure\Nthat all the materials are here on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.67,0:23:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We get our orders from the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.67,0:23:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the office
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.68,0:23:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,will tell us how many to make
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.48,0:23:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—maybe the specific volume number.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.51,0:23:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Braille Bibles come
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.58,0:23:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Wallkill printery\Non the Braille production floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.12,0:23:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Right at the end of the machine,\Nwe have a Braille paper roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.75,0:24:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We make sure\Nthat there’s nothing wrong with that roll,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.22,0:24:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it gets fed into the machine
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.89,0:24:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where it creates Braille\Non both sides of the page.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.96,0:24:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that,\Nit gets cut and punched.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.70,0:24:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We gather it\Nand do some quality inspection.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.20,0:24:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll bind it together;\Nwe’ll rivet each section into a binder
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.24,0:24:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that has been prelabeled\Nwith a volume number,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.74,0:24:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,do an inspection on it,\Npop it in a box, and then send it out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.38,0:24:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,To produce the English Bible in Braille\Ntakes about four and a half hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.45,0:24:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which then breaks out into 28 volumes,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.88,0:24:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Portuguese Bible \Nin Braille takes closer
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.65,0:24:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to five and a half hours,\Nand that breaks out into 32 volumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.92,0:24:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We did not start production with Genesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.09,0:24:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because we wanted the brothers\Nand sisters to be able to receive the volume
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.33,0:24:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be\Non the congregation Bible reading schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.33,0:24:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,at our midweek meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.80,0:24:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we receive\Nthe files for each volume,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.30,0:24:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s being printed and sent out\Nto our brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.41,0:24:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s important to me\Nto be able to read God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.78,0:24:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than just listening
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.95,0:25:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because I am a visual person.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.45,0:25:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the eyesight is gone, but I’m still visual.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.42,0:25:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I learn better from reading\Nthan I do from listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.69,0:25:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In my mind when I’m listening,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.26,0:25:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,my mind wanders,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.53,0:25:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but when I’m reading, I can stop
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.60,0:25:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditate on what I’m studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.30,0:25:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That helps me\Nwith my relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.27,0:25:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It has helped me a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.40,0:25:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because a lot of things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.84,0:25:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t have to look up
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.94,0:25:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s in plain English.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.71,0:25:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They have so many things\N in this new Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.54,0:25:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that I can use, like the outline.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.05,0:25:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get that outline\Nand find something fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.02,0:25:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the appendix,\Nthe word index,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.48,0:25:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the glossary.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.25,0:25:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,During the time of the Memorial,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.99,0:25:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to read the events\Nof the last week of Jesus’ life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.79,0:25:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I really enjoy reading with one hand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.36,0:25:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and pulling the other hand down
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.83,0:25:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and reading the footnotes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.00,0:25:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can participate more\Nin the midweek meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.64,0:26:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, in the section\N“Digging for Spiritual Gems,”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.71,0:26:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers always get someone\Nfrom the audience to read the scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.52,0:26:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So once I got the new Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.88,0:26:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I could raise my hand\Nand volunteer to read,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.55,0:26:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and so the whole meeting opened up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.06,0:26:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The revised edition
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.53,0:26:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,helps me be more effective at the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.33,0:26:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and it helps me to find
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.83,0:26:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.00,0:26:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the revision,\Nwhen he’d have a part on the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.41,0:26:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he would have to get his Brailler out\Nand have me dictate one sentence at a time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.78,0:26:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so he could type it all out\N—what he was going to use in his part.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.58,0:26:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is nice because he has
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.75,0:26:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the right wording\Nthat all the friends have.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.55,0:26:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I like to carry it from house to house,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.55,0:26:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so I can only take\Nthe one volume because they’re huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.86,0:26:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever the initial call is,\NI can take that scripture
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.36,0:26:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and see if the householder\Nwill let me read a scripture for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.20,0:27:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It means so much to be able to read\Nthe Scriptures and to do personal study.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.14,0:27:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I am very thankful for all the work\Nour brothers have done up in Wallkill.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.91,0:27:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate the effort
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.95,0:27:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that they’ve all gone through,\Nbecause that’s a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.28,0:27:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In Jehovah’s organization,\Nthey care for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.92,0:27:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so thankful\Nthat they had the Braille Bible for the blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.49,0:27:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what draws me closer to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.40,0:27:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—being able to study his Word\Nand look the scriptures up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.40,0:27:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The new Bible is personal to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.34,0:27:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like it was\Na personal answer to a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.24,0:27:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah supplied it because that’s\Nthe main thing I wanted to read,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.44,0:27:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am so thankful to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.38,0:27:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Like these brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.09,0:27:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,treasure the gift of God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.66,0:27:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray that Jehovah\Ncontinue to bless the efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.46,0:28:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the revised New World Translation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.43,0:28:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,available in more languages and formats.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.20,0:28:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,With the Bible and Christian publications,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.37,0:28:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re equipped to do\Nall we can in the preaching work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.64,0:28:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That desire to ‘fully accomplish our ministry’
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.95,0:28:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is captured in this month’s original song
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.85,0:28:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“All I Can Give.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.03,0:28:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,O heavenly Father,\NI want to give all I can give.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.24,0:28:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My desire is to please you\Nand love you as long as I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.38,0:29:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll help those who listen\Nto find in your Word what they need.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.23,0:29:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To preach and to teach\Nis the way I can really succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.57,0:29:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As I praise you, Jehovah,\Nmy faith’s getting stronger each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.28,0:29:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll reflect on my dedication.\NI’ll walk in your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.96,0:29:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,O heavenly Father,\Nto you I give praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.63,0:29:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to serve you\Nin so many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.80,0:29:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart is wide open\Nas long as I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.54,0:30:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I’ll love you\Nand give you all I can give.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.71,0:30:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole-souled devotion\Nand love for my brothers I’ll show.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.22,0:30:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Volunteering to play my part\Nis the best way I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.16,0:30:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m happier when I am giving\Nthan when I receive,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.17,0:31:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When I’m taking the time\Nto help others who may be in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.19,0:31:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As I praise you, Jehovah,\Nmy faith’s getting stronger each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.70,0:31:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll reflect on my dedication.\NI’ll walk in your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.64,0:31:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,O heavenly Father,\Nto you I give praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.51,0:31:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to serve you\Nin so many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.65,0:31:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart is wide open\Nas long as I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.16,0:31:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I’ll love you\Nand give you all I can give.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.67,0:32:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,O heavenly Father,\Nto you I give praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.17,0:32:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to serve you\Nin so many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.58,0:32:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart is wide open\Nas long as I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.99,0:32:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I’ll love you\Nand give you all I can give.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.74,0:32:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In what ways did you see\Nthe brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.27,0:32:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,giving all they could in the ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.07,0:32:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They witnessed at every opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.54,0:32:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They preached door to door,\Nin public witnessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.08,0:32:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,at businesses, informally,\Nand in remote areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.55,0:32:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They used our Teaching Toolbox,\Nincluding videos,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.22,0:32:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach people\Nin a language they really understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.93,0:33:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The ministry is an important way
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.80,0:33:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we imitate Jehovah’s love for people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.00,0:33:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We also want to imitate Jehovah’s holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.67,0:33:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Herd explained\Nwhy we strive to stay morally clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.68,0:33:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about keeping physically clean?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.61,0:33:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not always easy for busy Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.48,0:33:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.55,0:33:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,see how Grayson gives his son
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.89,0:33:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the loving counsel on cleanliness that he needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.86,0:33:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I graduated\Nfrom high school that summer
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.20,0:33:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and wanted to start\Nregular pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.10,0:33:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s my dad, Grayson.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.14,0:33:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad was having\Ncar trouble that morning
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.81,0:33:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and needed a ride to work,\Nso I gave him one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.21,0:33:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, my car\Nwas a little messy and smelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.26,0:34:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was winter,\Nand my car is pretty old anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.89,0:34:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So why bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.10,0:34:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When I get a new car,\Nthen I’ll keep it clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.50,0:34:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was making\Na big deal out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.64,0:34:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That morning was not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.35,0:34:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.09,0:34:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But later that evening,\NDad brought it up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.26,0:34:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time, it went better.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.50,0:34:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He showed me a picture of his first car.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.34,0:34:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked pretty old too.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.37,0:34:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that while our home\Nor car may not be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.17,0:34:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,fancy or luxurious,\Nit should be as clean and presentable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.14,0:34:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as circumstances allow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.51,0:35:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I still didn’t see what the big deal was.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.15,0:35:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, he explained\Nthat Jehovah is a clean God,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.35,0:35:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and from ancient times,\Nhe has always required
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.79,0:35:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that his people be a clean people.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.09,0:35:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the Mosaic Law\Nthat Jehovah gave to Israel,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.06,0:35:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,cleanness and worship\Nwere inseparable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.03,0:35:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It specified that priests were required
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.04,0:35:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to wash their hands and feet
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.04,0:35:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,before offering sacrifices to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.34,0:35:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,While in an unclean state, an Israelite
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.04,0:35:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,could not have any part in worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.88,0:35:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or it could mean death.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.88,0:35:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “I’m not an Israelite,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re not\Nunder the Mosaic Law anymore.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.89,0:35:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “True, but it gives us insight
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.26,0:35:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,into Jehovah’s thinking.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.36,0:35:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Law emphasized that cleanness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.90,0:35:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,was required\Nof all those who worshipped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.20,0:35:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Malachi 3:6 tells us,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.10,0:35:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Jehovah has not changed.’
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.24,0:36:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, he said something\Nthat really stuck with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.24,0:36:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Besides, it’s not all about us.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.05,0:36:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, he gave me a scripture to look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.42,0:36:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 2 Corinthians 6:3, 4:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.62,0:36:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“In no way are we giving\Nany cause for stumbling,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.63,0:36:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that no fault\Nmay be found with our ministry;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.10,0:36:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“but in every way
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.30,0:36:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we recommend ourselves as God’s ministers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.12,0:36:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that things like our appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.82,0:36:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,our homes, and our cars
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.76,0:36:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,—these can all be\Na silent witness to Jehovah in themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.66,0:36:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It made sense to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.23,0:36:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not all about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.53,0:36:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew what I had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.87,0:37:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did I clean my car,\Nbut later that year,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.78,0:37:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to turn in\Nmy application for pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.12,0:37:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m glad for the lesson\NI learned from my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.49,0:37:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not all about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.29,0:37:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in little ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.86,0:37:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we can reflect favorably\Non the God we love.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.20,0:37:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What made Grayson’s counsel effective?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.04,0:37:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Although he reacted to sitting in the dirty car,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.94,0:37:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,he waited until he was calm to give counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.01,0:37:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He based what he said\Non God’s standards in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.22,0:37:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And it took humility\Nfor his son to see that his cleanliness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.59,0:37:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,could affect how others\Nview Jehovah’s clean people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.59,0:38:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility helps us to accept correction,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.26,0:38:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but it can do even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.73,0:38:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the topic of this Bethel morning worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.20,0:38:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,wherein Brother Mark Noumair asks why humility
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.47,0:38:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was such an important lesson for Jesus’ apostles
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.18,0:38:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and why it still is for us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.11,0:38:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It is interesting that Peter gives counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.78,0:38:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,about cultivating humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.15,0:38:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn the clock back
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.49,0:38:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn why the quality of humility
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.99,0:38:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was indelibly etched
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.96,0:38:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mind and heart of Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.83,0:38:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s open our Bibles to Luke chapter 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.46,0:38:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In Luke chapter 22,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.50,0:38:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll find Jesus getting ready\Nfor that final Passover in 33 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.10,0:38:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Luke 22, starting in verse 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.77,0:38:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it is Thursday afternoon, Nisan 13,\Nand what happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.78,0:38:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 8: “Jesus sent Peter [there he is]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.38,0:38:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“and John, saying: ‘Go and get
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.59,0:39:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the Passover ready for us to eat.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.72,0:39:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Get it ready, Peter and John.’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.13,0:39:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 9: “They said to him:\N‘Where do you want us to get it ready?’”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.90,0:39:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They understood the instructions: Get it ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.20,0:39:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said to go into Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.20,0:39:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll find the man\Nwith the earthenware jar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.04,0:39:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 12: “And that man
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.07,0:39:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“will show you\Na large, furnished upper room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.18,0:39:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it ready there.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.88,0:39:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 13: “So they left \Nand found it just as he had told them,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.15,0:39:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and they prepared for the Passover.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.69,0:39:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it ready; prepare the Passover.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.79,0:39:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What would that include?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.23,0:39:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Bread, wine, oil for the lamps,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.23,0:39:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,lamb, a towel, a basin, water.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.87,0:39:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Basin and water
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.91,0:39:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—they knew \Nhow important washing feet was.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.74,0:40:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They witnessed when\NJesus reproved Simon the Pharisee
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.41,0:40:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with the statement: Simon,\N“you gave me no water for my feet.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.79,0:40:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Simon, you gave me no water.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.02,0:40:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You missed the mark on this one.’
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.56,0:40:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So as they stared\Nat that basin and water,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.00,0:40:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,as they prepared\Nand got the room ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.70,0:40:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,did they look at each other\Nand wonder:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.14,0:40:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who’s going to wash the feet?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.14,0:40:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’s going to do it?’
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.84,0:40:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They had a golden opportunity\Nto apply all the things that Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.68,0:40:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,had been teaching them\Nfor three and a half years on humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.78,0:40:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.78,0:40:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After three and a half years,\Nconduct yourself as a lesser one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.59,0:40:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t lord it over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.39,0:40:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to serve others and not be served.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.92,0:40:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This was it; this was the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.99,0:40:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They could have showed Jesus\Nthat they got the point; they got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.63,0:40:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They had time to think about it\Nand time to pray about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.63,0:40:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Thursday afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.53,0:40:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but now we progress\Nand let’s see what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.54,0:41:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s now progress\Nto the evening, and it’s Nisan 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.11,0:41:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s pick up the account in John chapter 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.71,0:41:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They got the room ready,\Nthey followed the instructions,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.38,0:41:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and now let’s go to John 13\Nand get John’s vantage point from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.32,0:41:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was there;\Nhe was with Peter getting it ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.36,0:41:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So now it’s 98 C.E.,\Nand John is writing this information.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.36,0:41:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He had time to reflect\Nand to think about this for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.40,0:41:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and now look what he says in verse 3:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.40,0:41:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.87,0:41:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“knowing that the Father\Nhad given all things into his hands
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.14,0:41:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he came from God\Nand was going to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.28,0:41:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing these things\N—he understood that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.85,0:41:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat back and said:\N‘Jesus knew who he was; he knew all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.42,0:41:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He had the full understanding of his dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.53,0:41:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew that he\Nhad been entrusted with all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.33,0:41:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.56,0:41:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew he was the second greatest\Npersonage in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.57,0:42:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew he was\N“the firstborn of all creation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.37,0:42:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew he had shared \Nwith his Father in creating all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.61,0:42:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He had knowledge of all this\N—knowing all these things.’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.38,0:42:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,John sits back; he writes this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.38,0:42:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then knowing this,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.75,0:42:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 4 is the contrast:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.82,0:42:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He got up from the evening meal\Nand laid aside his outer garments.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.82,0:42:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Taking a towel,\Nhe wraps it around his waist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.86,0:42:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‘After that, he puts the water\Ninto the basin
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.20,0:42:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and starts to wash\Nthe feet of the disciples
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.10,0:42:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and dry them off with the towel\Nthat was wrapped around him.’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.10,0:42:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing who He was,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.70,0:42:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,John said He did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.91,0:42:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But not only does John reflect\Non who Jesus was,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.04,0:42:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no, he reflects on why Jesus did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.68,0:42:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.78,0:42:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what John was interested in,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.12,0:42:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and we get that answer back in verse 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.39,0:42:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,where John says why:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.52,0:43:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Because he loved his own\Nthat were in the world;
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.59,0:43:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,he loved them to the end.’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.66,0:43:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,John said He “loved them to the end.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.47,0:43:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.87,0:43:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to instill in them qualities\Nthat would help them conquer the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.77,0:43:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities that would strengthen\Nthe Christian congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.24,0:43:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities such as unselfish love\Nand humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.41,0:43:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved them to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.41,0:43:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He never gave up on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.42,0:43:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They had their weaknesses,\Nbut he did not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.29,0:43:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for Peter, some 30 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.52,0:43:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s thinking about humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.79,0:43:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,John, some 60 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.16,0:43:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,after the lesson Jesus taught\Nabout humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.63,0:43:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s echoing loud and clear\Nin his mind and heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.47,0:43:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the fact remains\Nthat neither of them
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.81,0:43:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,had the humility at the time\Nto apply what Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.08,0:43:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,had been teaching them\Nfor three and a half years.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.41,0:43:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after John finished his writing, he sat back;
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.42,0:43:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,he was under inspiration;\Nhe finished that writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.29,0:44:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he sit back,\Nreread what he just wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.39,0:44:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps say to himself:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.06,0:44:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I wish I could have written
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.56,0:44:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that after Jesus washed the feet\Nof one or two of his disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.57,0:44:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I got up and washed the feet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.37,0:44:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‘of the rest of my brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.54,0:44:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I took that towel, and I imitated the Christ?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.14,0:44:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, Peter and I got up?’
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.35,0:44:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But the point is, they didn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.15,0:44:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.19,0:44:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t allow valuable lessons\Nthat Jesus teaches us
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.92,0:44:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to echo in our minds and hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.06,0:44:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,only after we missed\Nthe opportunity to apply them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.00,0:44:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a practical setting\Nfor us serving here at Bethel:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.97,0:44:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Even though I know\NI have the seniority
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.11,0:44:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‘—I have full knowledge of my seniority—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.91,0:44:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‘will I get up and fight the attitude\Nof entitlement?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.91,0:45:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have\Nauthority entrusted to me as the overseer;
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.85,0:45:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I am the overseer;\NI know that. I have full knowledge of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.02,0:45:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Fine, will I get up
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.66,0:45:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and roll my sleeves back\Nand do the grunt work?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.29,0:45:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Or do I just find pleasure\Nin giving orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.80,0:45:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have\Na wonderful privilege of service;
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.10,0:45:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know that; others know it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.80,0:45:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, but will I get up to train others?’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.98,0:45:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Jackson reminded us of this\Nat the last Gilead graduation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.35,0:45:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when he said to treasure your privileges,\Nbut don’t hoard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.72,0:45:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we have to get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.75,0:45:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes humility \Nto train others to take our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.62,0:45:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,‘As a brother or a sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.53,0:45:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have more experience\Nthan the other person in my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.40,0:45:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have the experience; I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.67,0:45:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I have more experience than my workmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.27,0:46:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Fine, but will I get up in all humility
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.28,0:46:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and share information that I have
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.15,0:46:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‘with others to make their job easier?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.38,0:46:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Or will I hold the knowledge I have hostage?’
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.39,0:46:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get up in all humility\Nand do these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.66,0:46:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can say that Jesus’ humble act,\Nas recorded here in John 13,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.66,0:46:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,has made a lasting\Nand indelible impression
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.60,0:46:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,not only on Peter and John\Nbut on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.74,0:46:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful lesson!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.57,0:46:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility will improve the way
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.58,0:46:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we carry out our theocratic assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.11,0:46:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It honors our fellow workers,\Nand it promotes unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.12,0:46:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Unified servants of God get things done.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.09,0:46:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In Peru,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.09,0:46:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,local brothers worked \Nwith international servants and volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.43,0:46:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to complete two new Assembly Halls.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.73,0:46:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In this report,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.73,0:47:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hear what the brothers\Nlearned from working together
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.00,0:47:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and how the new Assembly Halls
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.27,0:47:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are being used to glorify Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.13,0:47:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose whatever we give to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.20,0:47:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is little in comparison with what he gives to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.33,0:47:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And like Malachi 3:10 says, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.40,0:47:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we just have to ‘bring in the tenth part.’
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.04,0:47:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s really all that Jehovah is asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.04,0:47:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but he pours out a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.04,0:47:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And part of those blessings from Malachi 3:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.48,0:47:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I consider to be\Nthe friendships that we’ve gained.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.25,0:47:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, my favorite thing is the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.25,0:47:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s always just getting to work
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.39,0:47:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with your brothers every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.39,0:47:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The personalities shine through,\Neven with language differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.23,0:48:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You just make friends,\Nand you just get this taste
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.93,0:48:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of what the new world is going to be like.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.23,0:48:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Side by side with our brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.50,0:48:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve made parent figures\Nand brother and sister figures,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.94,0:48:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody just becomes\Npart of such a solid family.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.34,0:48:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Working along with the local brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.58,0:48:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,made it clear to me
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.08,0:48:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that we really are in the organization
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.45,0:48:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is directing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.72,0:48:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What I have seen is how Jehovah’s spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.72,0:48:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,operates in his organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.59,0:48:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There were many international servants here
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.66,0:48:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from various countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.70,0:48:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with different personalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.10,0:48:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,along with our local brothers\Nwith their distinct customs.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.37,0:48:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it was time to work, we were as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.98,0:48:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn’t a big guy, a little guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.31,0:48:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,someone more intelligent, or less intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.88,0:48:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We all formed one united team.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.82,0:49:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The language definitely was an issue for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.62,0:49:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At first I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.63,0:49:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Will I really be able to work with the brothers?’
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.83,0:49:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I didn’t understand the language,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.60,0:49:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how could I explain\Nthe work that had to be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.10,0:49:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, if you go in there with a good attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.64,0:49:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’re just having\Na good time working with your brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.91,0:49:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re not going to have too much of a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.78,0:49:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Smiles\N—they cross borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.65,0:49:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chiclayo dedication program
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.66,0:49:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,was held April 9, 2016,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.73,0:49:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Trujillo Assembly Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.76,0:49:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was dedicated shortly thereafter,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.16,0:49:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on July 31.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.14,0:49:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All present marveled with appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.04,0:49:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at seeing the facilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.64,0:49:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,their own new Assembly Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.68,0:50:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, we had to work a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.68,0:50:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe up to 15 days beforehand
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.15,0:50:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare a completely inappropriate site.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.06,0:50:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.49,0:50:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the brothers only need to maintain it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.69,0:50:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and simply arrive\Nin order to enjoy their assembly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.30,0:50:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure that this new Assembly Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.37,0:50:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,will strengthen the spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.13,0:50:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of our dear brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.64,0:50:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can say something about the video monitors:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.87,0:50:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ve revolutionized\NJehovah’s method of teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.81,0:50:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We get so much more out of the talks now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.92,0:50:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.98,0:50:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the gestures of the brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.55,0:50:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It really touches the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.55,0:50:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.86,0:50:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember more than 25 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.69,0:50:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to Jehovah and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.89,0:50:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah, please,\Npermit me at some point to see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.87,0:50:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,an Assembly Hall here.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.87,0:50:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And now Jehovah let me
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.87,0:50:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,be part of the buying process,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.87,0:51:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting the documentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.01,0:51:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and of being part of the construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.21,0:51:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember, and I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.61,0:51:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah answered my prayer.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.28,0:51:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it affected me
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.95,0:51:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing the construction progress
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.56,0:51:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because when we first arrived
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.56,0:51:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,at our project in Chiclayo,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.73,0:51:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what the brothers had
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.73,0:51:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they were using as an Assembly Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.70,0:51:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then to see the finished project
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.70,0:51:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that we see now,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.97,0:51:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so happy for the brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.91,0:51:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so beautiful, clean, neat, and tidy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.78,0:51:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like, in reality, for where it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.54,0:51:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s a little jewel within that whole city
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.58,0:51:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to me when I see the completed project.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.75,0:51:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know that brothers\Ndo just love to be able to care for that place,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.76,0:51:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to worship Jehovah there,\Nand to be with their brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.76,0:51:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing that will ever compare
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.46,0:51:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with this wonderful experience\Nwe’ve been able to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.80,0:52:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been great!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.21,0:52:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve enjoyed a wonderful program.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.88,0:52:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our videos showed us so many of the ways
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.78,0:52:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we can present our gift to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.15,0:52:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.15,0:52:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw our brothers, young and old,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.89,0:52:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,give their best in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.36,0:52:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation, at Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.76,0:52:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and on construction projects.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.00,0:52:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And we heard good counsel to be humble,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.13,0:52:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,morally clean, and physically clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.00,0:52:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And to conclude our program,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.31,0:52:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we have greetings\Nfrom our brothers and sisters in Chad.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.14,0:52:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Chad is located in north-central Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.71,0:52:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,With the Sahara Desert in the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.32,0:52:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,most of Chad’s more than 13 million people
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.15,0:52:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,live in the fertile southern regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.16,0:53:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Fewer than a thousand brothers live and preach
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.19,0:53:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in this vast field dotted with remote villages.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.40,0:53:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The capital city is N’Djamena.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.57,0:53:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Five congregations\Nare busy spreading the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.50,0:53:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in the city and its surrounding area.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.67,0:53:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One of these, just south of the capital,\Nis the Walia Congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.51,0:53:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They preach regularly along the Logone River,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.72,0:53:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where they often meet people\Ntraveling from faraway areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.69,0:53:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Their busy activity also helped to establish
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.69,0:53:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a new congregation in nearby Koundoul.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.76,0:53:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers in Koundoul and Walia
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.73,0:53:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,send us\Ntheir heartfelt Christian love and greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.20,0:53:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray for Jehovah to bless
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.37,0:53:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,their gifts of brotherly affection and self-sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.41,0:53:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for joining us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.94,0:53:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.38,0:54:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.
